# iCloud workspace: shell command rules

The workspace lives under `~/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/...` (iCloud path with spaces).

## Shell commands: use working_directory, NOT cd

The path has spaces. `cd "path"` in the sandbox fails. Instead, use the Shell tool's `working_directory` parameter:

```
working_directory: "/Users/nicholas.brookins/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/Documents/code/danger-finger"
command: PYTHON=/usr/bin/python3 make test-parametric
```

This works in the **default sandbox** — no `required_permissions: ["all"]` needed, no user approval prompt.

**NEVER** use `cd "/path/with spaces" && ...` — it causes sandbox quoting failures.
**NEVER** use `required_permissions: ["all"]` unless truly needed — it forces a user approval prompt.

## Broken venv

`.venv/` shebangs point to `/Users/nbrookins/...` (stale). Use `/usr/bin/python3` or `PYTHON=/usr/bin/python3 make ...` instead.
